1
00:00:17,852 --> 00:00:19,979
[wind howling]

2
00:00:28,612 --> 00:00:29,738
[Qifrey grunts]

3
00:00:29,905 --> 00:00:31,656
[ALAIRA] What's the point
of having a stairway

4
00:00:31,657 --> 00:00:33,533
if no one's going to use it?

5
00:00:33,534 --> 00:00:34,742
It's been a long time

6
00:00:34,743 --> 00:00:37,453
since you last came here
to the seabed.

7
00:00:37,454 --> 00:00:39,914
Problem child of the Great Hall.

8
00:00:39,915 --> 00:00:43,250
Those days are long past,
Alaira, charmed.

9
00:00:43,251 --> 00:00:44,878
Are they, now?

10
00:00:44,879 --> 00:00:46,420
As I understand it,

11
00:00:46,421 --> 00:00:48,423
you've been stirring up
trouble again.

12
00:00:49,633 --> 00:00:52,593
I know all about
your new apprentice.

13
00:00:52,594 --> 00:00:55,263
[QIFREY] Already?
Word travels fast.

14
00:00:55,806 --> 00:00:57,348
[ALAIRA] You think
she has the connection

15
00:00:57,349 --> 00:00:58,516
you're looking for?

16
00:00:58,517 --> 00:01:01,060
To the Brimmed Caps, that is?

17
00:01:02,646 --> 00:01:03,813
It's been four years

18
00:01:03,814 --> 00:01:05,773
since anyone's used
forbidden magic.

19
00:01:05,774 --> 00:01:06,942
She's a vital lead.

20
00:01:08,235 --> 00:01:10,404
That has nothing to do with it.

21
00:01:11,655 --> 00:01:14,072
And she's not my apprentice yet,

22
00:01:14,073 --> 00:01:15,533
she hasn't even been tested.

23
00:01:15,534 --> 00:01:17,159
[ALAIRA] Well,
what are you waiting for?

24
00:01:17,160 --> 00:01:18,745
[QIFREY] She's still new,

25
00:01:18,746 --> 00:01:20,413
and now is not the time.

26
00:01:20,414 --> 00:01:22,080
Ah, yes, of course.

27
00:01:22,081 --> 00:01:24,082
The test is held
at the Dadah Range,

28
00:01:24,083 --> 00:01:25,168
and this time of year.

29
00:01:25,460 --> 00:01:27,795
The elevation is going to be
at its highest point.

30
00:01:27,796 --> 00:01:30,673
I wouldn't dream of testing
someone in such conditions.

31
00:01:30,674 --> 00:01:32,718
They could be killed.

32
00:01:35,345 --> 00:01:37,806
[♪ opening theme song playing]

33
00:03:15,863 --> 00:03:17,656
[birds chirping]

34
00:03:18,115 --> 00:03:19,825
[COCO] Um, Agott?

35
00:03:20,659 --> 00:03:22,660
Are you sure about this?

36
00:03:22,661 --> 00:03:24,244
With Master Qifrey gone...

37
00:03:24,245 --> 00:03:25,246
THE DADAH RANGE TEST

38
00:03:25,580 --> 00:03:26,622
It's something you're going
to have to do alone,

39
00:03:26,623 --> 00:03:28,041
whether he's here or not.

40
00:03:28,042 --> 00:03:29,917
[COCO] But aren't we
rushing things a bit?

41
00:03:29,918 --> 00:03:31,251
I just got here!

42
00:03:31,252 --> 00:03:33,546
I passed this test
when I was ten years old.

43
00:03:33,547 --> 00:03:35,213
It's required of everyone
who wishes

44
00:03:35,214 --> 00:03:38,009
to become an apprentice,
including yourself.

45
00:03:38,010 --> 00:03:39,218
I see.

46
00:03:40,303 --> 00:03:43,221
[AGOTT] The first test is called
"Consent of the Crown."

47
00:03:43,222 --> 00:03:45,808
You're only allowed the use
of three contraptions

48
00:03:45,809 --> 00:03:47,643
and your components.

49
00:03:47,644 --> 00:03:50,563
Your objective is to reach
the summit of the Dadah Range

50
00:03:50,564 --> 00:03:52,899
purely on your own power,
and when you do,

51
00:03:52,900 --> 00:03:55,776
to pick the Diadem Herb
that grows there.

52
00:03:55,777 --> 00:03:56,861
The Guidance Orb,

53
00:03:56,862 --> 00:03:58,278
to point the way
to your destination,

54
00:03:58,279 --> 00:04:00,781
and the Vapor Bubble,
for drinking water.

55
00:04:00,782 --> 00:04:02,658
That's probably
all you can handle

56
00:04:02,659 --> 00:04:03,827
for the moment.

57
00:04:05,079 --> 00:04:07,288
Now, begone.

58
00:04:11,960 --> 00:04:13,878
- One last thing.
- Mm?

59
00:04:13,879 --> 00:04:16,173
Could I possibly have
some shoes like yours?

60
00:04:16,506 --> 00:04:17,882
Some shoes?

61
00:04:17,883 --> 00:04:19,593
[COCO] They'd count as
my third contraption, right?

62
00:04:19,968 --> 00:04:22,220
You and Master Qifrey
both have them.

63
00:04:22,221 --> 00:04:24,638
The soles light up
when you fly.

64
00:04:24,639 --> 00:04:29,185
So, uh... I was wondering
if maybe, you might, uh...

65
00:04:29,186 --> 00:04:32,188
be willing to lend me a pair?

66
00:04:32,189 --> 00:04:33,940
Eh...

67
00:04:33,941 --> 00:04:35,983
Of course not! That was
too much to ask! Sorry!

68
00:04:35,984 --> 00:04:37,443
Forget I said anything!

69
00:04:37,444 --> 00:04:39,487
[Agott inhales, exhales deeply]

70
00:04:42,532 --> 00:04:43,699
[Coco gasps]

71
00:04:43,700 --> 00:04:45,619
You may borrow mine.

72
00:04:45,994 --> 00:04:47,661
And with that settled...

73
00:04:47,662 --> 00:04:48,913
[COCO] Thank you.

74
00:04:48,914 --> 00:04:50,330
[AGOTT]
...it's time you were off!

75
00:04:50,331 --> 00:04:51,416
[Coco grunts]

76
00:04:52,126 --> 00:04:54,919
Oh, I almost forgot.
When it comes to this test,

77
00:04:54,920 --> 00:04:56,837
you won't be getting
any second chances.

78
00:04:56,838 --> 00:04:59,257
If you should fail,
you'll be disqualified

79
00:04:59,258 --> 00:05:01,592
from ever becoming
Master Qifrey's apprentice,

80
00:05:01,593 --> 00:05:03,678
and required
to leave the atelier.

81
00:05:04,846 --> 00:05:06,181
[Coco gasps]

82
00:05:12,146 --> 00:05:14,396
- [wings flapping]
- [Coco whimpers]

83
00:05:14,397 --> 00:05:17,399
All of a sudden I'm terrified.

84
00:05:17,400 --> 00:05:19,235
But I can't turn back.

85
00:05:19,236 --> 00:05:21,280
I have to do all I can!

86
00:05:22,656 --> 00:05:25,700
So this is a Guidance Orb.
But how do I use it?

87
00:05:27,452 --> 00:05:28,702
[clinking]

88
00:05:28,703 --> 00:05:29,704
[Coco exclaims]

89
00:05:37,087 --> 00:05:39,840
Is it telling me
I should go this way?

90
00:05:42,134 --> 00:05:43,467
Right!

91
00:05:43,468 --> 00:05:45,970
A little mountain-climbing?
Simple!

92
00:05:45,971 --> 00:05:47,429
[yelps]

93
00:05:47,430 --> 00:05:48,597
[grunts]

94
00:05:48,598 --> 00:05:50,141
♪

95
00:05:50,142 --> 00:05:51,892
I can do it!

96
00:05:51,893 --> 00:05:57,606
After all, Agott did it
when she was ten!

97
00:05:57,607 --> 00:05:58,692
[yelps]

98
00:06:00,277 --> 00:06:03,529
If she could do it that young,
then surely I...

99
00:06:03,530 --> 00:06:06,533
[Coco screams]

100
00:06:07,951 --> 00:06:09,785
Surely, I...

101
00:06:09,786 --> 00:06:11,163
[yelps]

102
00:06:14,249 --> 00:06:15,416
[gasps]

103
00:06:18,795 --> 00:06:20,130
No.

104
00:06:20,922 --> 00:06:22,590
It can't be.

105
00:06:30,473 --> 00:06:32,016
This is it?

106
00:06:32,017 --> 00:06:34,560
This is the Dadah Range?

107
00:06:34,561 --> 00:06:36,104
[footsteps]

108
00:06:38,899 --> 00:06:42,069
The Guidance Orb
is pointing directly at it.

109
00:06:42,319 --> 00:06:44,071
That must be it, then.

110
00:06:44,487 --> 00:06:46,156
[sighs]

111
00:06:48,325 --> 00:06:51,703
Someone could have told me
it would be floating in the air.

112
00:06:52,829 --> 00:06:54,206
[bird screeching]

113
00:06:56,791 --> 00:06:58,251
[Coco gasps]

114
00:06:58,252 --> 00:06:59,627
[COCO] Yes!

115
00:06:59,961 --> 00:07:02,755
I knew it was smart
to ask her for these!

116
00:07:02,756 --> 00:07:04,674
Fly!

117
00:07:06,176 --> 00:07:07,301
Uh?

118
00:07:07,302 --> 00:07:09,221
- [wind blows]
- [Coco grunts]

119
00:07:15,560 --> 00:07:16,811
[Coco sighs]

120
00:07:17,979 --> 00:07:20,147
Half the Casting Seal
on one foot,

121
00:07:20,148 --> 00:07:21,858
and half on the other.

122
00:07:28,990 --> 00:07:33,036
If I put them together,
and align them perfectly.

123
00:07:34,037 --> 00:07:35,247
[Coco gasps]

124
00:07:35,789 --> 00:07:38,125
[exclaims]

125
00:07:39,542 --> 00:07:41,253
[laughs]

126
00:07:41,628 --> 00:07:45,048
Look at me!
I'm floating off the ground!

127
00:07:45,464 --> 00:07:47,507
[whimpers]

128
00:07:47,508 --> 00:07:50,053
[screams]

129
00:07:52,306 --> 00:07:55,015
Master Qifrey
had it exactly right.

130
00:07:55,016 --> 00:07:57,393
I'm an awkward,
clumsy little foal.

131
00:07:57,394 --> 00:07:59,562
- [bird screeching]
- [gasps]

132
00:08:00,981 --> 00:08:02,315
And yet...

133
00:08:02,316 --> 00:08:04,192
[bird screeching]

134
00:08:06,820 --> 00:08:08,487
I can fly.

135
00:08:09,739 --> 00:08:11,158
♪

136
00:08:11,532 --> 00:08:14,619
If I fly, I'll reach
the summit in no time!

137
00:08:15,578 --> 00:08:16,788
Now...

138
00:08:17,080 --> 00:08:18,373
Here I go!

139
00:08:21,001 --> 00:08:22,377
[thuds]

140
00:08:22,961 --> 00:08:24,295
[QIFREY] Don't you worry.

141
00:08:24,296 --> 00:08:26,797
You'll be running wild
in no time at all.

142
00:08:26,798 --> 00:08:28,008
[Coco grunts]

143
00:08:28,342 --> 00:08:30,468
[COCO] Running wild.

144
00:08:30,469 --> 00:08:32,012
Running wild.

145
00:08:54,826 --> 00:08:57,370
Could you please
process this application?

146
00:08:57,371 --> 00:09:01,123
- Right. Thotrey, number twelve.
- Of course.

147
00:09:01,124 --> 00:09:03,000
You know, you wouldn't
have to travel

148
00:09:03,001 --> 00:09:05,461
for this sort of thing
if you lived in the Great Hall.

149
00:09:05,462 --> 00:09:08,255
Your apprentices
would be welcome here, too.

150
00:09:08,256 --> 00:09:10,216
The Great Hall is
the witches' stronghold.

151
00:09:10,217 --> 00:09:12,759
Everything a witch could need
can be found here.

152
00:09:12,760 --> 00:09:16,264
And so, when I need something,
I come.

153
00:09:17,015 --> 00:09:18,391
All right, here you are!

154
00:09:18,392 --> 00:09:19,892
[QIFREY] Thank you.

155
00:09:19,893 --> 00:09:22,729
Your hate for the Great Hall
runs deep, eh?

156
00:09:23,313 --> 00:09:25,981
Well, keep an eye
on those apprentices of yours.

157
00:09:25,982 --> 00:09:27,733
With children that age,

158
00:09:27,734 --> 00:09:29,485
you never know
what they might get up to

159
00:09:29,486 --> 00:09:31,405
when left to their own devices.

160
00:09:33,114 --> 00:09:35,492
[whimpering]

161
00:09:36,868 --> 00:09:38,285
[COCO] That's good!

162
00:09:38,286 --> 00:09:40,787
I think I'm getting better
at maintaining my balance!

163
00:09:40,788 --> 00:09:43,083
Maybe I should try going
a little higher.

164
00:09:45,210 --> 00:09:48,838
[grunts, screams]

165
00:09:55,594 --> 00:09:57,472
♪

166
00:09:59,182 --> 00:10:01,434
[grunts, exhales]

167
00:10:01,435 --> 00:10:02,809
[Coco sighs]

168
00:10:02,810 --> 00:10:04,061
[COCO] Huh?

169
00:10:04,062 --> 00:10:05,855
[squeaks]

170
00:10:09,359 --> 00:10:10,985
[Coco gasps]

171
00:10:11,403 --> 00:10:13,821
[screams]

172
00:10:14,573 --> 00:10:16,324
[screams]

173
00:10:20,828 --> 00:10:23,039
[panting]

174
00:10:24,165 --> 00:10:27,752
[COCO] A brushbuddy!
I've never seen one before!

175
00:10:35,093 --> 00:10:36,635
[Coco sighs]

176
00:10:38,597 --> 00:10:39,598
[groans]

177
00:10:39,889 --> 00:10:42,892
Agott's shoes are covered
with mud now. Great.

178
00:10:44,311 --> 00:10:45,812
[brushbuddy chirps]

179
00:10:51,485 --> 00:10:52,943
[Coco gasps softly]

180
00:10:52,944 --> 00:10:55,862
[gasps] No, no, what happened?
The seal is coming off!

181
00:10:55,863 --> 00:10:58,115
It's all my fault,
I wiped it off!

182
00:10:58,116 --> 00:11:00,159
Oh, no, oh, no,
oh, no! What now?

183
00:11:00,160 --> 00:11:01,911
I know! I'll just draw it
back on!

184
00:11:02,412 --> 00:11:03,788
[Coco squeals nervously]

185
00:11:04,331 --> 00:11:05,581
Would you look at that,

186
00:11:05,582 --> 00:11:07,917
the Conjuring Ink spilled
in my bag somehow.

187
00:11:09,877 --> 00:11:11,003
[brushbuddy sniffs]

188
00:11:11,004 --> 00:11:12,130
[squeaks]

189
00:11:12,671 --> 00:11:14,715
What am I supposed to do?

190
00:11:16,801 --> 00:11:18,512
Is it all over?

191
00:11:20,763 --> 00:11:24,475
So, uh... Agott, have you
seen Coco around?

192
00:11:24,476 --> 00:11:26,768
It's going to be dinner time
pretty soon.

193
00:11:26,769 --> 00:11:28,395
Coco's not here right now.

194
00:11:28,396 --> 00:11:31,398
She left for the Dadah Range
a while ago to take her test.

195
00:11:31,399 --> 00:11:32,816
What, all by herself?

196
00:11:32,817 --> 00:11:35,194
But she just got to the atelier
a short time ago!

197
00:11:35,195 --> 00:11:37,737
Why didn't you stop her?
Really, Agott!

198
00:11:37,738 --> 00:11:40,575
[AGOTT] Most would have taken
the test before coming here.

199
00:11:41,742 --> 00:11:43,286
You're right, but...

200
00:11:43,995 --> 00:11:46,746
[AGOTT] If she can't pass
a test as simple as that,

201
00:11:46,747 --> 00:11:49,750
then she has no business
being an apprentice.

202
00:11:50,377 --> 00:11:51,961
Understand.

203
00:11:52,086 --> 00:11:55,172
I refuse to tolerate those
who can't reach my level.

204
00:11:55,173 --> 00:11:57,342
Their presence
has no value to me.

205
00:11:57,925 --> 00:12:01,179
Especially if they're also
Outsiders.

206
00:12:02,013 --> 00:12:03,430
There's no need to worry.

207
00:12:03,431 --> 00:12:05,933
She'll be back soon enough,
after she's failed.

208
00:12:06,643 --> 00:12:07,894
During this season,

209
00:12:08,019 --> 00:12:11,022
the Dadah Range reaches
its greatest altitude.

210
00:12:11,439 --> 00:12:12,898
She'll never reach such heights

211
00:12:12,899 --> 00:12:15,568
with only my Sylph Shoes
to carry her.

212
00:12:15,569 --> 00:12:16,943
She's ignorant of the rules

213
00:12:16,944 --> 00:12:18,946
and unaware of the danger
she's put herself in.

214
00:12:20,739 --> 00:12:22,449
I don't want
to share our world

215
00:12:22,450 --> 00:12:23,742
with someone like that.

216
00:12:25,995 --> 00:12:27,913
[Tetia whines]

217
00:12:27,914 --> 00:12:30,290
So are you not eating?

218
00:12:30,291 --> 00:12:33,419
[groans] I will, but...

219
00:12:33,420 --> 00:12:37,090
I guess I'm just feeling
a little bit down right now.

220
00:12:38,091 --> 00:12:39,174
[Richeh gasps softly]

221
00:12:39,175 --> 00:12:40,343
[TETIA] Huh?

222
00:12:41,553 --> 00:12:42,844
[RICHEH] Seconds.

223
00:12:42,845 --> 00:12:44,555
Am I really the only one

224
00:12:44,556 --> 00:12:46,265
who's the least bit worried
around here?

225
00:12:46,266 --> 00:12:50,353
What can we do, except wait
for Master Qifrey to return?

226
00:12:51,187 --> 00:12:52,438
[Tetia groans]

227
00:12:52,439 --> 00:12:54,691
[Coco grunting]

228
00:12:59,820 --> 00:13:01,739
[Coco sighs] It's no use.

229
00:13:01,740 --> 00:13:05,033
I tried drawing it back on
with what's left of the ink,

230
00:13:05,034 --> 00:13:07,785
but I'm still not getting off
the ground at all.

231
00:13:07,786 --> 00:13:09,037
[sighs]

232
00:13:09,038 --> 00:13:11,832
The ink's smearing
because the shoes are wet.

233
00:13:19,299 --> 00:13:22,636
What if I drew on the soles
of my feet?

234
00:13:25,305 --> 00:13:27,098
[Coco gasps]

235
00:13:30,560 --> 00:13:32,145
[Coco gasps]

236
00:13:32,479 --> 00:13:33,688
No, I can't!

237
00:13:33,854 --> 00:13:37,066
Magic directly involving
the human body is forbidden.

238
00:13:38,985 --> 00:13:40,736
I don't have the first clue

239
00:13:40,737 --> 00:13:43,657
of what kind of spell would help
at a time like this.

240
00:13:44,157 --> 00:13:45,950
[brushbuddy squeaks]

241
00:13:48,244 --> 00:13:51,623
I guess Agott was right,
wasn't she?

242
00:13:59,922 --> 00:14:02,091
[Tetia exclaims]

243
00:14:02,592 --> 00:14:05,594
[COCO] Anyone can learn
how to draw spells,

244
00:14:05,595 --> 00:14:08,597
but that doesn't mean
they'll be good at using magic.

245
00:14:08,598 --> 00:14:11,517
Maybe I need to accept
that only someone special

246
00:14:11,518 --> 00:14:13,101
can become a witch.

247
00:14:13,102 --> 00:14:14,436
[BOTH] Huh?

248
00:14:14,437 --> 00:14:15,772
[Coco gasps]

249
00:14:16,356 --> 00:14:17,940
♪

250
00:14:21,611 --> 00:14:23,779
[COCO] All of them
have been drawing spells

251
00:14:23,780 --> 00:14:25,532
since they were children.

252
00:14:25,990 --> 00:14:28,867
It's not something
I could ever...

253
00:14:36,584 --> 00:14:37,752
[Coco gasps]

254
00:14:41,756 --> 00:14:43,006
[COCO'S MOTHER] Hm.

255
00:14:43,007 --> 00:14:44,425
[Coco gasps] Mm.

256
00:14:47,721 --> 00:14:50,598
There... Nice and straight.

257
00:14:51,057 --> 00:14:53,226
- [Coco's mother gasps]
- [Coco screams]

258
00:14:57,856 --> 00:15:00,775
- [COCO'S MOTHER] Coco.
- Boo! [laughs]

259
00:15:02,819 --> 00:15:03,944
[COCO] Uh?

260
00:15:05,363 --> 00:15:06,988
[QIFREY] My!

261
00:15:06,989 --> 00:15:08,990
I had no idea
this village possessed

262
00:15:08,991 --> 00:15:10,159
such a skilled artisan.

263
00:15:11,870 --> 00:15:13,495
This is real magic.

264
00:15:13,496 --> 00:15:14,706
[Coco gasps]

265
00:15:16,666 --> 00:15:17,915
[brushbuddy squeals]

266
00:15:17,916 --> 00:15:19,084
That's it.

267
00:15:19,085 --> 00:15:20,336
♪

268
00:15:23,715 --> 00:15:25,800
[COCO] I have my own magic!

269
00:15:26,760 --> 00:15:28,302
[wind blowing]

270
00:15:31,556 --> 00:15:33,433
[Coco panting]

271
00:15:39,272 --> 00:15:40,398
[brushbuddy squeaks]

272
00:15:48,656 --> 00:15:51,868
[COCO] If I let a little water
soak in and dilute it...

273
00:15:56,955 --> 00:16:00,208
My cape's a little stiff
from all the dried mud.

274
00:16:00,209 --> 00:16:02,168
I think I can draw on it.

275
00:16:02,169 --> 00:16:03,420
[brushbuddy squeaks]

276
00:16:03,421 --> 00:16:04,923
♪

277
00:16:29,029 --> 00:16:30,739
[QIFREY] It's natural
to be unsteady

278
00:16:30,740 --> 00:16:32,951
when you're getting
used to something new.

279
00:16:35,745 --> 00:16:37,245
[COCO] In that case,

280
00:16:37,246 --> 00:16:39,833
how about something
I'm already used to?

281
00:16:40,959 --> 00:16:45,672
My fingers begin to dance
of their own accord.

282
00:16:46,130 --> 00:16:47,423
Freely.

283
00:16:52,512 --> 00:16:53,804
[brushbuddy squeaks softly]

284
00:16:53,805 --> 00:16:55,555
[wind blowing]

285
00:16:55,556 --> 00:16:56,724
[COCO] There!

286
00:16:57,308 --> 00:16:58,809
Good morning, Brushbuddy!

287
00:16:58,810 --> 00:17:00,812
You've made yourself at home,
haven't you?

288
00:17:02,020 --> 00:17:04,272
It's a pretty ugly Casting Seal,
I know.

289
00:17:04,273 --> 00:17:06,274
Ideally, the sigil
should be centered,

290
00:17:06,275 --> 00:17:08,485
and the signs
are supposed to be uniform.

291
00:17:08,486 --> 00:17:09,570
[brushbuddy squeaks softly]

292
00:17:10,112 --> 00:17:11,864
[COCO] I just learned
if they aren't balanced,

293
00:17:11,865 --> 00:17:14,491
it can send too much energy
in one direction.

294
00:17:14,492 --> 00:17:16,242
So I wondered
what would happen

295
00:17:16,243 --> 00:17:17,787
if I made one long on purpose!

296
00:17:18,287 --> 00:17:20,874
I can't be sure
if it'll work, though.

297
00:17:21,248 --> 00:17:23,501
- [brushbuddy squeals]
- [Coco yelps]

298
00:17:23,626 --> 00:17:25,795
[laughs]

299
00:17:29,256 --> 00:17:30,757
You want to come with me?

300
00:17:30,758 --> 00:17:31,801
[brushbuddy squeaks]

301
00:17:32,134 --> 00:17:34,303
All right, but I need you
to hold on tight for me.

302
00:17:35,638 --> 00:17:37,431
And now to close the ring.

303
00:17:39,517 --> 00:17:40,810
[wind gushing]

304
00:17:41,978 --> 00:17:44,564
- [Coco gasps]
- [brushbuddy squeaks]

305
00:17:45,690 --> 00:17:47,399
[COCO] What? What's happening?

306
00:17:47,400 --> 00:17:49,108
I don't understand!

307
00:17:49,109 --> 00:17:51,403
Did I get
the sign's direction wrong?

308
00:17:51,404 --> 00:17:54,615
- [Coco screaming]
- [brushbuddy squeaking]

309
00:18:01,414 --> 00:18:02,957
[wood creaking]

310
00:18:04,082 --> 00:18:07,003
[Coco continues screaming]

311
00:18:09,087 --> 00:18:10,631
[Coco grunting]

312
00:18:24,270 --> 00:18:25,896
I did it, brushbuddy!

313
00:18:25,897 --> 00:18:29,106
I'm flying, with my own magic!

314
00:18:29,107 --> 00:18:31,651
My dream has finally
come to life.

315
00:18:31,652 --> 00:18:33,613
A cloak of flight!

316
00:18:36,574 --> 00:18:38,034
♪

317
00:18:45,541 --> 00:18:47,793
In the end,
I learned to use magic

318
00:18:47,794 --> 00:18:50,296
using what I learned
from helping Mom.

319
00:18:50,630 --> 00:18:52,339
Unbelievable.

320
00:18:55,093 --> 00:18:57,260
But the Diadem Herb's up higher!

321
00:18:57,261 --> 00:18:59,346
♪

322
00:19:04,518 --> 00:19:06,269
[brushbuddy squeaks]

323
00:19:06,270 --> 00:19:07,772
[Coco gasps]

324
00:19:11,025 --> 00:19:12,485
[COCO] There it is!

325
00:19:16,990 --> 00:19:18,490
[Coco screams, grunts]

326
00:19:18,491 --> 00:19:19,659
♪

327
00:19:29,209 --> 00:19:30,544
[Coco grunting]

328
00:19:39,720 --> 00:19:40,972
[brushbuddy squeaks]

329
00:19:41,681 --> 00:19:42,974
[screaming]

330
00:19:51,315 --> 00:19:52,441
[Coco grunting]

331
00:19:55,736 --> 00:19:57,195
♪

332
00:19:58,948 --> 00:20:01,826
[Coco exclaims, laughs]

333
00:20:05,955 --> 00:20:08,749
[Coco pants]

334
00:20:12,170 --> 00:20:13,420
[COCO] Mom...

335
00:20:13,713 --> 00:20:15,297
[whimpers]

336
00:20:15,923 --> 00:20:17,175
[grunts]

337
00:20:21,054 --> 00:20:23,805
[COCO] Hold on, Mom!
Wait for me!

338
00:20:23,806 --> 00:20:28,186
I don't know how yet,
but I will make things right!

339
00:20:30,813 --> 00:20:31,939
[QIFREY] What?

340
00:20:32,148 --> 00:20:34,733
You're saying Coco went
to the Dadah Range alone

341
00:20:34,734 --> 00:20:36,860
- to be tested?
- [TETIA] Mm-hm. Mm-hm.

342
00:20:36,861 --> 00:20:38,403
It's too dangerous!

343
00:20:38,404 --> 00:20:40,237
I need to go
and save her at once!

344
00:20:40,238 --> 00:20:42,408
But if you interfere,
she'll fail the test!

345
00:20:42,616 --> 00:20:44,201
[QIFREY]
It was too soon for her

346
00:20:44,202 --> 00:20:45,952
to attempt it
in the first place.

347
00:20:45,953 --> 00:20:47,787
She hasn't been living
around magic

348
00:20:47,788 --> 00:20:49,081
her whole life like we have.

349
00:20:49,082 --> 00:20:51,876
And if anything were
to happen to Coco,

350
00:20:52,626 --> 00:20:55,003
we'd lose so much
more than just her.

351
00:20:55,004 --> 00:20:56,380
There.

352
00:21:00,593 --> 00:21:01,760
[COCO] Uh?

353
00:21:01,761 --> 00:21:03,803
- [brushbuddy squeals]
- Hello.

354
00:21:03,804 --> 00:21:05,222
[QIFREY AND TETIA] Coco!

355
00:21:05,223 --> 00:21:07,515
[cries] Thank goodness!

356
00:21:07,516 --> 00:21:09,475
I'm so glad you're all right!

357
00:21:09,476 --> 00:21:13,063
I can't tell you how sick
with worry I was about you!

358
00:21:13,064 --> 00:21:14,190
[brushbuddy squeaks]

359
00:21:14,523 --> 00:21:16,067
Agott, look!

360
00:21:16,483 --> 00:21:19,652
The "Consent of the Crown."
I did it.

361
00:21:19,653 --> 00:21:21,030
[Agott grunts softly]

362
00:21:22,907 --> 00:21:25,576
This is the proof
I needed to get, right?

363
00:21:26,410 --> 00:21:27,703
- [brushbuddy squeaks]
- [COCO] Huh?

364
00:21:28,537 --> 00:21:29,747
Uh...

365
00:21:35,293 --> 00:21:39,422
Coco, in the absence of
proper training and preparation,

366
00:21:39,423 --> 00:21:42,885
meddling with magic
can prove extremely dangerous.

367
00:21:43,177 --> 00:21:44,886
I thought you'd learned that.

368
00:21:44,887 --> 00:21:46,680
- [brushbuddy squeaks]
- [Coco sighs]

369
00:21:47,181 --> 00:21:50,349
That test could very easily
have cost you your life.

370
00:21:50,350 --> 00:21:52,685
You must never do
anything like that again.

371
00:21:52,686 --> 00:21:55,982
I understand, and I'm sorry.

372
00:21:57,942 --> 00:22:00,944
Besides, you needn't have
endangered yourself

373
00:22:00,945 --> 00:22:01,946
to prove anything.

374
00:22:02,113 --> 00:22:04,948
Because you're already
my new apprentice.

375
00:22:04,949 --> 00:22:07,575
[Tetia squeals, laughs]

376
00:22:07,576 --> 00:22:09,745
[♪ closing theme song playing]

377
00:22:12,414 --> 00:22:14,541
- [Coco exclaims]
- [brushbuddy squeaks]

378
00:22:18,212 --> 00:22:20,505
[gasps] This is...

379
00:22:20,506 --> 00:22:22,633
[brushbuddy squeals]

380
00:22:24,677 --> 00:22:27,679
[QIFREY] I give you
the mark of a witch.

381
00:22:27,680 --> 00:22:30,056
A symbol of our pride,

382
00:22:30,057 --> 00:22:33,978
and of our solemn vow
never to use magic for evil.

383
00:22:44,697 --> 00:22:47,615
[QIFREY] As long as
it rests upon your head,

384
00:22:47,616 --> 00:22:49,785
you mustn't forget its weight.

385
00:22:50,161 --> 00:22:52,787
The pointed cap
shall watch over you,

386
00:22:52,788 --> 00:22:54,874
and your magic.

387
00:22:55,708 --> 00:22:58,002
See that you take
good care of it.

388
00:22:59,170 --> 00:23:00,462
Right!

389
00:23:01,088 --> 00:23:04,090
Now, shall we
all return upstairs?

390
00:23:04,091 --> 00:23:05,551
We shall!

391
00:23:06,344 --> 00:23:07,677
[Coco's stomach grumbles]

392
00:23:07,678 --> 00:23:08,971
[Tetia chuckles]

393
00:23:09,387 --> 00:23:11,848
I think someone needs
a bite to eat!

394
00:23:11,849 --> 00:23:14,267
And more importantly, a bath.

395
00:23:14,268 --> 00:23:16,020
♪

396
00:23:32,245 --> 00:23:34,705
[WITCH] The seed has sprouted.

397
00:23:35,413 --> 00:23:39,919
EPISODE 4:
MEETINGS IN KALHN

